---
title: Stuffed Zucchini Boats with Mushroom Duxelles, Quinoa, and Parmesan
description: Zucchini is the perfect vessel for stuffing—once scooped out, their seedy centers form a tiny boat for filling. Finely chopped mushrooms are sautéed with butter and shallot for a riff on mushroom duxelles, a classic French preparation. Folded into a quinoa stuffing, it’s divine!
